title: Sense and Sensibility
creator: Jane Austen
description: LibriVox recording of Sense and Sensibility by Jane Austen. Read by Karen Savage. When Mr Henry Dashwood dies, with his estate entailed to his son and grandson, his wife and three daughters are left in reduced circumstances. In their new home at Barton Cottage, the two older sisters, Elinor and Marianne, experience both romance and heartache. Will they find true happiness? (Introduction by Karen Savage) M4B audiobook of complete book For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
